      "content": "The concept of a \"welfare trap\" is a legitimate concern that policymakers must address, as it highlights the disincentive created by poorly structured benefits. However, the solution is not to dismantle the safety net, but to reform it to ensure that earning more always results in a net gain. A robust safety net that phases out gradually is the necessary economic mechanism to support workers while still incentivizing them to seek better employment.",
